  body
    //-
      div.loading-container(ng-if="!loaded")
        div.loading
          div.layer.one
          div.layer.two
          div.layer.three
          h1 Loading
    div.container
      button.toggle-layers.ng-hide.fix-top-left(data-ng-click="layers.open ? layers.open = false : layers.open = true", data-ng-show="layer.active !== 'home' && !layers.open", data-ng-if="layer.active !== 'home' && !layers.open")
        i.icon.layers-icon.white
      div#layers.layers(data-ng-class="{ transformed: layers.open }")
        div.layer.one(data-layer="0", data-ng-class="{front: layer.active === 'home'}")
          div.layer-content
            div.text
              h1.content Hello
              p.content My name is Tejas Kumar.
              p.content I am a person of many 
                span#letter-container.letter-container
                  span.letter(data-expand-letter) l
                  span.letter(data-expand-letter) a
                  span.letter(data-expand-letter) y
                  span.letter(data-expand-letter) e
                  span.letter(data-expand-letter) r
                  span.letter(data-expand-letter) s
                  span.letter(data-expand-letter) .
              button.content.vertical-space.invisible.see-layers(ng-click="layers.open ? layers.open = false : layers.open = true")
                i.icon.layers-icon.black 
                span See Layers
        div.layer.two(data-layer="1", data-ng-class="{front: layer.active === 'work'}")
          h1.descriptor(data-ng-click="layers.open = true") Work
          div.layer-content(ng-if="layer.active === 'work'")
            section
              p.big-text I create beautiful things with technology, currently for a company called <a target="_blank" href="http://grow.qa" rel="noindex">grow</a>. I believe in beautiful products &mdash; inside and out: from code to user interface.
              p.big-text Below are some of the technologies I love and use on a daily basis.
              ul.technologies
                li(data-ng-repeat="tech in technologies", data-ng-class="tech", style="background-image: url('img/tech/{{tech.slug}}.png')")
                  div(class="text", data-ng-bind-html="tech.text")
        div.layer.three(data-layer="2", data-ng-class="{front: layer.active === 'music'}")
          h1.descriptor(data-ng-click="layers.open = true") Music
          div.layer-content(data-ng-if="layer.active === 'music'")
            section
              p.big-text I love music. I play the guitar, the bass, and <em>my vocal cords</em>. I sometimes write songs and dabble in audio production. 
              p.big-text I also <em>teach</em> music. 
              p.big-text <span class="link" ng-click="layer.active = 'contact'">Get in touch</span> if you&rsquo;re interested in learning music or just jamming. Below is some music I&rsquo;ve made.
            div.embed-container
              iframe(scrolling="no", frameborder="no", src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/users/7808007&amp;auto_play=false&amp;hide_related=false&amp;show_comments=true&amp;show_user=true&amp;show_reposts=false&amp;visual=true")
        div.layer.four(data-layer="3", data-ng-class="{front: layer.active === 'personal'}")
          h1.descriptor.white(data-ng-click="layers.open = true") About
          div.layer-content(data-ng-if="layer.active === 'personal'")
            section
              p.big-text I was born with <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hemophilia" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">hemophilia</a>. It&rsquo;s nasty. I&rsquo;ve lived with it all my life. Living with hemophilia, I could not do many things that regular folk can do: like go to school regularly as a child. In a year, I would attend about <em>two weeks</em> worth of school.
              p.big-text Because of this, I had a lot of free time to do whatever interested me. I spent that free time playing with &mdash; and eventually getting really good at &mdash; <em>computer stuff</em>.
              p.big-text I&rsquo;ve lived in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qatar" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Qatar</a> for the past 18 years. I believe in miracles. Why? I&rsquo;m glad you asked:
                ul.big-text
                  li Hemophilia can be deadly if not treated.
                  li Treatment is expensive: it would cost about &dollar;17,000 <em>per week</em> to keep me healthy today.
                  li My family was relocated to Qatar in 1997. Qatar was relatively unknown in 1997.
                  li Shortly after moving here, my family found out this country is one of the only countries in the <em>world</em> where this treatment is free for expats.
              p.big-text Miracles are real. If you&rsquo;d like to talk, <span class="link" ng-click="layer.active = 'contact'">hit me up</span>.
        div.layer.five(data-layer="4", data-ng-class="{front: layer.active === 'contact'}")
          h1.descriptor.white(data-ng-click="layers.open = true") Contact
          div.layer-content(data-ng-if="layer.active === 'contact'")
            section
              p.big-text If you&rsquo;d like to get in touch, <a href="mailto:hello@tej.as">send me an email</a>. I can also be found on <a href="http://fb.com/tejaskumar" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">facebook</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/tejaskumar_" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">twitter</a> and <a href="http://instagram.com/tejaskumar" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">instagram.</a> I look forward to hearing from you!
              div.embed-container
                iframe.instagram(src="//instansive.com/widgets/59b0d69e741e7345987d6afe43fbd6a3efdfb655.html", allowtransparency="true")
